article.headline: Siena 83, Dartmouth 69
article.story: HANOVER, N.H. (AP) -- Michael Haddix hit 12-of-18 shots from the field as Siena pulled away in the second half to beat Dartmouth 83-69 Wednesday night. Trailing by as many as eight points, Siena (1-2) closed the first half with a 10-2 run to tie the score at 32 at halftime. Dartmouth (0-4) led by five early in the second half, but after grabbing a 65-63 lead with seven minutes remaining, Siena went on a 10-2 run to take the first double-digit lead either team held all night. Dartmouth never got closer than six points the rest of the way. Haddix, who led all scorers with 28 points, also led the Saints in rebounds, with nine. Kenny Hasbrouck was a perfect 8-for-8 from the field and 6-for-6 from the line while scoring all of his 23 points. Johnathan Ball scored 18 points in 24 minutes and DeVon Mosley had 16 points for Dartmouth, which got 11 points apiece from Jason Meyer and Alex Barnett, and eight rebounds from Jarrett Mathis.
